						<section class="overview__content overview__content_1">
				<ul class="overview__params params params_lead">
					<li class="params__years params__item">
						<span class="params__years__value">3</span>
						<span class="params__years__title params__item__title">years</span>
					</li>
					<li class="params__item">
						<span class="params__item__title">Full-time</span>
						<span class="params__item__note">Duration</span>
					</li>
					<li class="params__item">
						<span class="params__item__title">19 900 EUR</span>
						<span class="params__item__note">Tuition Fee/Year</span>
					</li>
					<li class="params__item">
						<span class="params__item__title">240 ECTS</span>
						<span class="params__item__note">ECTS</span>
					</li>
					<li class="params__item">
						<span class="params__item__title">English</span>
						<span class="params__item__note">Language of Instruction</span>
					</li>
					<li class="params__item">
						<span class="params__item__title">All year round</span>
						<span class="params__item__note">Application Period</span>
					</li>
				</ul>
				<div class="overview__text text">
										<p>Computer Science BSc programme offers students with basic analytic skills and a strong aptitude for mathematics, programming, and logical reasoning the best in the world opportunity for in-depth study of Computer science concepts and theories in highly practical and cutting edge educational environment. Core computer science skills such as software development, object orientated programming (OOP) and database engineering form the basis of the curriculum, with advanced exploratory courses such as data mining to follow. 

</p>
										<p>Throughout the study students will continuously acquire an understanding of real-world computing needs, as demonstrated by their ability to address technical issues involving computing problems encountered in industry, government and graduate programs.  </p>
									</div>
				<a href="/courses/computer-science?curriculum-Bachelor" class="action overview__action">
					<span class="action__text">See full curriculum</span>
				</a>
				<strong class="overview__title">Programme structure</strong>
				<!-- year -->

								<div class="overview__year overview__year_1 overview__year_last_false">
					<dl class="overview__year__number overview__year__number_1">
						<dd class="overview__year__number__value">1</dd>
						<dd class="overview__year__number__label">year</dd>
					</dl>
					<div class="overview__year__content">
						<div class="overview__year__text text">
														<p>In the first year, students obtain the foundational knowledge in mathematics and the basics of programming upon which students will develop understanding of programming and computer science during following years. The courses are mostly given in a form of lectures and takeaway coursework. By the end of this year, students will be able to write programmes and use primary computer science tools.</p>
													</div>
						<div class="overview__year__additional">
							<strong class="overview__year__title">Modules</strong>
							<ul class="overview__year__modules">
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_1">Combinatorics and Graphs</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_1">Foundations of Programming: C/C++</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_1">Calculus – 1</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_1">Practical Unix</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_1">Linear Algebra - 1</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_1">Algorithms and Data Structures – 1</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_1">Combinatorics and Graphs – 2</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_1">Object Oriented Programming: Python</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_1">Calculus – 2</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_1">Algorithms and Data Structures – 2</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_1">Linear Algebra – 2</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_1">Computer Organisation and Systems</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_1">Combinatorics and Graphs – 3</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_1">Operating Systems</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_1">Calculus – 3</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_1">Capstone Project - 1</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_1">Seminars & Workshops - 1</li>
															</ul>
						</div>
												<span class="more">
							<span class="more__text">More</span>
							<span class="more__arrow"></span>

											</div>
				</div>
								<div class="overview__year overview__year_2 overview__year_last_false">
					<dl class="overview__year__number overview__year__number_2">
						<dd class="overview__year__number__value">2</dd>
						<dd class="overview__year__number__label">year</dd>
					</dl>
					<div class="overview__year__content">
						<div class="overview__year__text text">
														<p>In the second year the students will be offered both math courses in the field of discrete mathematics and courses in the field of software development and programming languages. Most courses require practical coursework and a course project enabling students to get a feel for the challenges and approaches used in this field. The students will also begin developing software for the Capstone project.
</p>
														<p>By the end of this year, students will be able to write programmes and use primary computer science tools. </p>
													</div>
						<div class="overview__year__additional">
							<strong class="overview__year__title">Modules</strong>
							<ul class="overview__year__modules">
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_2">Introduction to Probability</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_2">Introduction to Statistics</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_2">Java Programming</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_2">Foundations of Mathematical Logic</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_2">Functional Programming</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_2">Introduction to Optimization</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_2">Machine Learning – 1</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_2">Formal Language Theory</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_2">Compilers</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_2">Introduction to Computer Networking</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_2">Database Systems Principles</li>

																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_2">Introduction to Cryptography</li>

																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_2">Capstone Project - 2</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_2">Seminars & Workshops - 2</li>

												<span class="more">
							<span class="more__text">More</span>
							<span class="more__arrow"></span>
						</span>
											</div>
				</div>
								<div class="overview__year overview__year_3 overview__year_last_true">
					<dl class="overview__year__number overview__year__number_3">
						<dd class="overview__year__number__value">3</dd>
						<dd class="overview__year__number__label">year</dd>
					</dl>
					<div class="overview__year__content">
						<div class="overview__year__text text">
														<p>In the third year, students will primarily focus on key computer science subjects including computational theory and cryptography. The practical side of the programme is focused on in-depth understanding of parallel computing, databases, compilers.
</p>
														<p>At the end of the third year, students will have sufficient theoretical and programming background to tackle computer science problems in professional real world scenarios. A significant amount of time will be dedicated to the development of the Capstone project.  The courses are taught by researchers and professionals who practice the courses they teach either academically or by sharing their professional experiences in their field. The goal of the final year is to expose students to a range of real-world applications of the material that they've learned to ensure seamless transition into a professional roles.</p>
													</div>
						<div class="overview__year__additional">
							<strong class="overview__year__title">Modules</strong>
							<ul class="overview__year__modules">

																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_3">Mobile Application Development</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_3">Technical Project Management</li>
																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_3">Algorithms in Bioinformatics</li>

						<section class="overview__content overview__content_2">
				<ul class="overview__params params params_lead">
					<li class="params__years params__item">
						<span class="params__years__value">2</span>
						<span class="params__years__title params__item__title">years</span>
					</li>
					<li class="params__item">
						<span class="params__item__title">Full-time</span>
						<span class="params__item__note">Duration</span>

						<span class="params__item__title">22 900 EUR</span>
						<span class="params__item__note">Tuition Fee/Year</span>
					</li>
					<li class="params__item">
						<span class="params__item__title">120 ECTS</span>
						<span class="params__item__note">ECTS</span>
					</li>
					<li class="params__item">
						<span class="params__item__title">English</span>
						<span class="params__item__note">Language of Instruction</span>
					</li>
					<li class="params__item">
						<span class="params__item__title">All year round</span>
						<span class="params__item__note">Application Period</span>
					</li>
				</ul>
				<div class="overview__text text">
										<p>The MSc programme is designed for those who desire to deepen their
comprehension of all aspects of the computer sciences. Applicants could be
graduates from other degrees with a strong mathematical core, or those
continuing their academic pursuit after achieving a BSc in computer science.</p>
										<p>The programme is heavily geared towards developing students’ professional skills needed for employment, while being able to adapt to rapidly changing technology, to work effectively, professionally and ethically in computing-related professions, as demonstrated by their communications, teamwork and leadership skills. It also motivates and engages students in life-long learning, including entering graduate programmes in Computer Science and related fields.</p>
									</div>
				<a href="/courses/computer-science?curriculum-Master" class="action overview__action">
					<span class="action__text">See full curriculum</span>
				</a>
				<strong class="overview__title">Programme structure</strong>
				<!-- year -->

								<div class="overview__year overview__year_1 overview__year_last_false">
					<dl class="overview__year__number overview__year__number_1">
						<dd class="overview__year__number__value">1</dd>
						<dd class="overview__year__number__label">year</dd>
					</dl>
					<div class="overview__year__content">
						<div class="overview__year__text text">
														<p>Students begin the programme already having foundational
knowledge of programming and mathematics including data
structures and algorithms, statistics and machine learning.
During the first year their knowledge of mathematics,
programming and data analysis will be significantly extended.
The programme also offers opportunity to learn the key soft skills for
the professional world including technical project management,
writing and presenting. </p>
														<p>Finally during the first year students are
expected to attend many of the talks and workshops offered by
the university and being work on the capstone project.</p>
													</div>
						<div class="overview__year__additional">
							<strong class="overview__year__title">Modules</strong>
							<ul class="overview__year__modules">

																<li class="overview__year__modules__item overview__year__modules__item_year_1">Theory of Probability and Statistics</li>

<!-- Program leadership -->
<section class="section" id="leadership">
	<div class="section__content i-content">
		<i class="section__decor"></i>
		<h2 class="section__title title">
						<span class="title__part">Programme</span>
						<span class="title__part">leadership</span>
					</h2>
				<article class="person">
			<div class="person__content">
				<div class="person__name">
					<span class="person__name__first">KONSTANTIN </span>
					<span class="person__name__second">MERTSALOV</span>
				</div>
				<div class="person__summary">Faculty Leader
Computer Science</div>
				<div class="person__about">
					<div class="person__about__text text">
												<p>Konstantin Mertsalov is European Director
of Development at Rational Enterprise, a
globally leading software development
company specialising in enterprise
information management.</p>
											</div>
					<div class="person__about__text person__about__text_hidden text">
												<p>Originally from Russia, he moved to New
York in 1998 to study Computer Science
and Applied Mathematics , and continued
his academic career with a Rensselaer
Polytechnic Institute PhD on large dynamic
social networks. He's an expert on
machine learning, information diffusion in
social network, semantic web search,
unstructured data, big data and data
analytics in general. He developed U Rank,
a search engine that allows people to
organise, edit and annotate search results
as well as share information.
Konstantin aims to lead the Harbour.Space
Data Science programme with unbridled
enthusiasm about the relatively new field,
and he’s determined to use his industry
knowledge to share, teach and create for
the future with his students.</p>
											</div>
										<span class="more">
						<span class="more__text">More</span>
						<span class="more__arrow"></span>
					</span>
									</div>
			</div>
			<div class="person__photo">
				<figure class="person__photo__inner"><img src="/sites/default/files/pleader/Konstantin Mertsalov_2_1.png" alt="" /></figure>
			</div>
		</article>
			</div>
</section>
<!--/Program leadership -->

<!-- Career path -->
<section class="career section" id="career">
	<div class="section__content i-content">
		<i class="section__decor"></i>
		<h2 class="section__title title">
						<span class="title__part">Career path</span>
					</h2>
		<div class="section__description text">
			<p>Every career looks different: it depends on individual aspirations as a well as changes in the industry. We’ve selected some stories to illustrate and celebrate the diversity of the various career paths.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="career__steps steps">
			<ul class="steps__content">
								<li class="steps__item">
					<div class="steps__item__content">
						<div class="steps__item__picture">
							<i class="steps__item__icon" data-icon="paper-plane"></i>
						</div>
						<div class="steps__item__name">Junior Software<br />Engineer</div>
						<div class="steps__item__text">As part of the development team,
junior software engineers learn to
apply the knowledge in Computer
Science obtained at the university to
practical problems at the workplace.
While handling entry level tasks, junior
software engineer quickly builds up
the experience necessary for taking on
more responsibility at the next step of
the career ladder.</div>
					</div>
				</li>
								<li class="steps__item">
					<div class="steps__item__content">
						<div class="steps__item__picture">
							<i class="steps__item__icon" data-icon="propeller-plane"></i>
						</div>
						<div class="steps__item__name">Software<br />Engineer</div>
						<div class="steps__item__text">Software engineer takes on the
responsibility for the development of
efficient and accurate software. The
key knowledge and skills at this level
include a deep understanding of the
key programming concepts, software
development experience, attention to
detail, and focus on the quality
and performance. The bulk of software
is developed at this level.</div>
					</div>
				</li>
								<li class="steps__item">
					<div class="steps__item__content">
						<div class="steps__item__picture">
							<i class="steps__item__icon" data-icon="reactive-plane"></i>
						</div>
						<div class="steps__item__name">Senior Software<br />Engineer</div>
						<div class="steps__item__text">The senior developer is an expert in
software engineering best practices
and the force driving software quality.
At this level, the engineer also takes on
coaching and mentoring
responsibilities to help other members
of the team to reach their highest
potential.</div>
					</div>
				</li>
								<li class="steps__item">
					<div class="steps__item__content">
						<div class="steps__item__picture">
							<i class="steps__item__icon" data-icon="airship"></i>
						</div>
						<div class="steps__item__name">Systems<br />Architect</div>
						<div class="steps__item__text">As a guru of a technical team, the
systems architect possesses a deep
understanding of programming and
computer science in general as well as
a strategic vision of the technical
evolution of the software product. The
systems architect brings in the
expertise in system design and the
modelling skills as well as knowledge
of technical frameworks and
components. It is also often the
responsibility of the systems architect
to develop the technical component of
the requirements specification to
ensure a consistent and
coherent software product.</div>
					</div>
				</li>
								<li class="steps__item">
					<div class="steps__item__content">
						<div class="steps__item__picture">
							<i class="steps__item__icon" data-icon="rocket"></i>
						</div>
						<div class="steps__item__name">Director of<br />Development</div>
						<div class="steps__item__text">As a leader of the engineering team,
the director of development
orchestrates the range of talent and
abilities the team members possess to
ensure the timely and efficient
development of software product.
Director of development succeeds by
understanding the business
requirements, mastering technical
project management, learning to
accurately estimate work effort, and
demonstrating first-grade team
leadership.</div>
					</div>
				</li>
								<li class="steps__item">
					<div class="steps__item__content">
						<div class="steps__item__picture">
							<i class="steps__item__icon" data-icon="ufo"></i>
						</div>
						<div class="steps__item__name">Chief Technology<br />Officer</div>
						<div class="steps__item__text">Chief technology officer is a business
leader with a big picture view of every
aspect of the technological side of the
organisation. The CTO understands
the current state of business as well as
the target benchmarks and is
responsible for enrolling technology to
advance business in the right
direction. The responsibilities of the
CTO often include leading the
development, information
technologies, support, technical
operations, and infrastructure
departments.</div>
					</div>
				</li>
							</ul>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
<!--/Career path -->

<!-- Quotes -->
<section class="quotes">
	<ul class="quotes__list">
				<li class="quotes__item">
			<div class="quotes__item__content">
				<span class="quotes__item__picture"><img src="/sites/default/files/quotes/google-logo-vector-free-download copy_1.png" alt="" /></span>
				<strong class="quotes__item__title"></strong>
                <span class="quotes__item__text">
                    <i class="quotes__item__text__before"></i>
                    <span class="quotes__item__text__inner">Software engineers develop the next-generation technologies that change how millions of users connect,
explore, and interact with information and one another. </span>
                    <i class="quotes__item__text__after"></i>
                </span>
			</div>
		</li>
				<li class="quotes__item">
